        The messenger — a traveling plant I don't recognize, all wrapped leaves and patient demeanor — is given a place of honor; they've carried Elder Heartwood's wisdom across three territories. That means something.

        Holloway says, "We thank you for bringing Elder Heartwood's understanding to us — your service to the network is recognized and valued."

        The messenger inclines slightly and says, "It is an honor to carry such wisdom — may it serve your need."

        The room feels charged — hopeful. Everyone here believes this response will change everything.

        Holloway says, "Please — share Elder Heartwood's wisdom."

        The messenger settles more firmly, preparing.

